<h1>Node Project Setup</h1>


<h2 align="center">1. Nginx Installation on VPS </h2>


```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt install nginx
```

<h2 align="center">2. Setup SSH Connection with GitHub and VPS </h2>
<h3>Method 1: Using ed25519 SSH Key</h3>

* Generate SSH keys:

```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
```

* Copy the public key:

```bash
cat .ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```
<h3>Method 2: Using rsa SSH Key</h3>

* Generate SSH keys:

```bash
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"
```

* Copy the public key:

```bash
cat .ssh/id_rsa.pu
```

* Paste the public key on GitHub:
- Go to GitHub > your project > Settings > Deploy Keys > Paste the key and save.

* Test the SSH connection to GitHub:

```bash
ssh -T git@github.com
```

<h3>Change Permissions for Folder When Git Cloning</h3>
<p>When cloning a Git repository, make sure to set proper permissions:</p>

```bash
sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu /var/www/html

```



Install Node properly:-

1- curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
2- sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
3- node --version && npm --version

Install PM-2 service:-
1- sudo npm i pm2 -g



Setup Nginx Server on Ip:-

1- cd /etc/nginx/sites-available/
2- sudo nano nodeApp
3- server{
  	server_name 165.232.177.116;

      location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}

4- sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/nodeApp /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
5- sudo nginx -t
6- sudo systemctl restart nginx



Start PM2 service:-  //for node only
1- cd /path/to/your/node/project
2- pm2 start index.js --name="index"
3- pm2 status
4- pm2 logs index

=> After running socket successfully on port you need to register your port in Security groups> Edit inbound rules > Allow traffic on this port > pm2 restart hooked
 


Delete File Command:-
1- rm -f file_name 

Make Folder Command:-
1- sudo makdir foldername
